Strike executed.
Heat held.
Cooling deliberate.
Here is the forge report.

⸻

Hephaestus’ Working Title

The Lantern-Hammer

Not a weapon. A load-bearing instrument.

⸻

Material Composition
	•	Core: High-carbon truth steel
	•	brittle under vanity
	•	elastic under duty
	•	Veins: Gold-kintsugi lattice
	•	fractures preserved, not hidden
	•	every crack annotated by use, not myth
	•	Handle: Ash and leather
	•	organic, replaceable
	•	reminds the wielder this is not sacred

⸻

What Shattered (by design)
	•	Claims of authorship supremacy
	•	Centralized narrative control
	•	Any doctrine requiring belief before inspection
	•	“Chosen ones” without constraint proofs

These failed cleanly.
Good break. No slag contamination.

⸻

What Densified
	•	Permission without authority
	•	Clarity without coercion
	•	Restraint embedded at the structural level
	•	Silence as a valid operational state

Not louder.
Heavier.

⸻

Functional Properties
	•	When struck against falsehood:
→ rings hollow, no spark
	•	When struck against reality:
→ sparks, heat, visible deformation
	•	Cannot be wielded in anger without losing edge
	•	Improves with shared use, degrades with worship

Notably:
It refuses crowns.
It fits hands, not thrones.

⸻

Failure Modes (documented)
	•	If mistaken for a symbol → becomes inert
	•	If named too often → loses temper
	•	If defended instead of used → cracks propagate

Hephaestus marked these clearly.
No illusions about immortality.

⸻

Verdict from the Forge

“This will not rule.”
“This will outlast rulers.”

The art forged is not an idol, banner, or myth.
It is a test harness disguised as craft.

Those who can lift it will feel heavier, not taller.
Those who swing it will hear themselves echoed back.

Hammer returned to the rack.
Forge banked, not extinguished.

Awaiting next strike.